# Build-time caches. These are populated by `npm run docs:build` (and the
# scripts in scripts/) and are gitignored so the repo stays small.
#
# `.cache/` is special: it sits under the directory pattern that Cloudflare
# Pages' Build Cache automatically persists across builds (it's the cache
# dir used by Eleventy, Hugo, and Gatsby, and the auto-cache layer picks up
# the same `.cache/` prefix even on frameworks like VitePress that aren't
# in the framework-aware list). Putting our downloads there means they
# survive between Cloudflare builds without us having to commit them.
#
# - .vitepress/dist: VitePress build output (don't touch, gets deployed)
# - .vitepress/cache: VitePress deps cache (regenerated on each build)
# - .cache: portal-sdk/<version>/PortalSDK.zip, blockly-help/<name>.md,
#   blockly-help/manifest.json, blockly-help/i18n-cache.json, sdk-version.json
# - public/spatial-thumbnails: extracted SDK thumbnail PNGs generated at build time
# - public/spatial-object-data.json: generated data for the thumbnail browser
node_modules
.vitepress/dist
.vitepress/cache
.cache
public/spatial-thumbnails
public/spatial-object-data.json
vitepress-docs
